{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f6312022-1d65-490b-92bb-e6ebbef84720","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but is listed before it. Let me fix this:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_1ikx4pHczsrhgBHjw1WCIv","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-6c3aac65241d477c8bdbfdb27f050d00/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-6c3aac65241d477c8bdbfdb27f050d00/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"d9284af1-e7e1-48de-98ee-91ce5d1a3528","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters. Files must be listed in dependency order in the `.fsproj` file. Currently:\n\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first - it depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`)\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second - it defines the types used by Services\n3. `Program.fs` is listed last - it depends on both\n\nThe fix is to reorder so `Domain.fs` comes before `Services.fs`:\n1. `Domain.fs` \n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":425,"requestId":"5C08:1CFDE0:1E962F6:2267FC5:6A07C8B8"},"id":"a43064b5-b3b3-4643-97b6-9955984bbaf0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:30:40.110Z","parentId":"427f3d6f-0775-4ce8-8ae4-107890d487df"}
